when we create a new local branch,
if we want to push it on server we have a error "UPSTREAM ERROR"
it means he doesn't know what is the related branch on server
we should "LINK" them.

"git branch -vv"        //this command show the branches we linked

Note: we push all branches on server
      but we don't link them yet
      (if we switch to one of them and make a push, we get error)
      (we just link the main branch)

  bugfix/login-form       7b7a5dc fixbug login form
  bugfix/signup-form      7c4a76d fix bug
  cherry-branch           a23232a step 5
  conflict-branch         5c8ff89 simulate conflict
  feature/change-password 7685de6 commit on feature
* main                    d1f97d7 [origin/main: ahead 1] release                     //we just link the main branch []
  overhall-4.7            e24c60a overhall 4,7
  pick-file               b4cf159 just one commit contain multiple file changes
  rebase-branch           1c23bc0 change some file on rebase-branch


1. we create a new branch as "LAST-BRANCH"
   we don't create any link yet on him

  bugfix/login-form       7b7a5dc fixbug login form
  bugfix/signup-form      7c4a76d fix bug
  cherry-branch           a23232a step 5
  conflict-branch         5c8ff89 simulate conflict
  feature/change-password 7685de6 commit on feature
* last-branch             dc5731f share branch                                       //we are here
  main                    dc5731f [origin/main: ahead 2] share branch                //we have not link him to origin like other branches
  overhall-4.7            e24c60a overhall 4,7
  pick-file               b4cf159 just one commit contain multiple file changes
  rebase-branch           1c23bc0 change some file on rebase-branch


Note: we can see all branches on remote server (github) by:
      "git branch -r"

    origin/HEAD -> origin/main              //we have all these branches on server
    origin/bugfix/login-form                //we have not the "LAST-BRANCH" yet!
    origin/bugfix/signup-form               //just main branch has linked to local branches! (git branch -vv" )
    origin/cherry-branch
    origin/conflict-branch
    origin/feature/change-password
    origin/main
    origin/overhall-4.7
    origin/pick-file
    origin/rebase-branch

2. link the "LAST-BRANCH" to server:
   "git push -u origin last-branch"         //u stand for upstream

  bugfix/login-form       7b7a5dc fixbug login form
  bugfix/signup-form      7c4a76d fix bug
  cherry-branch           a23232a step 5
  conflict-branch         5c8ff89 simulate conflict
  feature/change-password 7685de6 commit on feature
* last-branch             dc5731f [origin/last-branch] share branch                 //has link
  main                    dc5731f [origin/main: ahead 2] share branch               //has link
  overhall-4.7            e24c60a overhall 4,7
  pick-file               b4cf159 just one commit contain multiple file changes
  rebase-branch           1c23bc0 change some file on rebase-branch

3. commit current file on "last-branch"
   and push him to server.

Note: we can just push main and last-branch
      the other branches have not upstream yet!
      (although they are exist on server)

4. merge the "last-branch to main"

Note: github show the branches that never merged to main
      (like LAST-BRANCH before step 4)

5. we can remove the branch from server
   "git push -d origin last-branch"

Note: this will remove the branch from server
      but it will remain on local!